<br>
Sounds to me like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Planar Abilities&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are really spells, except they only work on the planes.  If that is the case, then perhaps the proposed mage summoned only mezz and charm should be planar abilities, since in fact they would appear only to be useful on the planes.  On the other hand, perhaps there are reuse timer issues that make that impractical.<br>
<br>
But they do not sound like skills.<br>
<br>
It sounds like a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;kludge&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to distinguish PoP-only spells from spells that are in the expansion, but work outside PoP.<br>
<br>
If there are no new actual skills, like AA skills, I will be a bit disappointed.  I like skills that modify my outcomes, like the caster archetype skills.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
